<TITLE> 500 families marooned as Padma River rages </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 23 (bdnews24.com)The Padma River was flowing 21cm above the danger mark at Goalundo point on Sunday, leaving low-lying areas in Faridpur Sadar and Char Bhadrashan upazilas inundated, a Water Development Board official said. The banks of the Padma River in at least two places in Char Bhadrashan upazila are now suffering from severe erosion, Faridpur WDB executive engineer Md Rafiqullah told bdnews24.com. "At least 500 families in Gadadhardangi, Bhajandangi and Sadipur have been marooned as floodwater inundated low-lying areas," said Md Akteruzzaman, a union member of ward seven in Aliabad, Faridpur Sadar. Pupils at Sadipur Government Primary School and Gadadhardangi Government Primary School are taking their examinations on roadside benches after water inundated their classrooms, said Akteruzzaman. bdn
